{"questionId":"5366495","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p style=\"text-align:left;\">The table gives data relating to the two moons of Mars.</p>\n<table style=\"height:68px;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;\" border=\"1\" width=\"245\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">Moon&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">\n<em>T</em> / hour</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">\n<em>r</em> / Mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;\">Phobos</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">7.66</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">9.38</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;\">Deimos</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">30.4</td>\n<td style=\"width:74.8295px;text-align:center;\">-</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi></mrow></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>Equates centripetal force (with Newton’s law of gravitation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi><mi>r</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mi>ω</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><mi>M</mi><mi>m</mi></mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>)</p>\n<p><em><strong>OR</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mi>ω</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;✓</p>\n<p><br>Uses both equation correctly with clear re-arrangement&nbsp;✓</p>","meta":{"questionId":"5366495","referenceCode":"EXE.2.SL.TZ0.12a","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"Show that k=1GM.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["D. Fields","D. Fields","D.1 Gravitational fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
